    "pfs": "Standard",
    "aonid": 3586,
    "game-obj": "Equipment",
    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "This thick, red liquid has a pungent\u2014but not unpleasant\u2014smell. You pour the oil onto a weapon when activating it. If the weapon has damaged a creature within the last 10 minutes, the most recent creature damaged by the weapon regains the listed number of Hit Points. The creature is then temporarily immune to *Digly's oil of sympathy* for 10 minutes.  \n   \n The magic relies on the malice behind the attack, so the weapon must have been used against an enemy of the attacker. In other words, someone can't voluntarily take damage from a friend's weapon, then heal from it\u2014a fact that made it very difficult for Sir Kenelm Digly to test the oil during its development.",
        "level": 1,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Rare",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 137,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
                "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "rare"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Consumable",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 36,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 454,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "07336d377bbfcf8d760f34f32f513526",
                "text": "An item with this trait can be used only once. Unless stated otherwise, it\u2019s destroyed after activation. Consumable items include alchemical items and magical consumables such as scrolls and talismans. A character can Craft consumable items in batches of four.",
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Healing",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 89,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 457",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 457",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 457,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "46d51374c2ada72347818dbac1edd7a3",
                "text": "A healing effect restores a creature\u2019s body, typically by restoring Hit Points, but sometimes by removing diseases or other debilitating effects.",
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Magical",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 103,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
                "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Oil",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 121,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 257",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 257",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 257,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "ae3604d98ffc303ee0eb84f9c3281d28",
                "text": "Oils are magical gels, ointments, pastes, or salves that are typically applied to an object and are used up in the process.",
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
